title: For Sale:  Remington-Elliot .32RF Ringfinger Derringer
postcontent:
Remington-Elliot Derringer .32RF Ringfinger.  Manufactured by E. Remington & Sons, Ilion, NY, between 1883 and 1888.  Production was estimated to 17,500.  This gun is in working order with the same serial number (12453) on both frame and barrel. Bores are dull with minimal evidence of grooves and lands. Grips are hard rubber.  Note the letter “B” on the left side of the frame, just above the top of the left grip. The Remington Society of America indicates that there may be two slightly different models of this gun. Guns with the letter “B” have a higher frame where it cradles the barrel cluster.  Additional photos available.
This gun has been in my family, probably since it was purchased by my great grandfather, passed to my grandfather, then to my father, and now to me.  From what I know about my great grandfather, the notches may be real.
Postal money order or certified check please.
